The paper discusses the implementation of empathic agents using a multi-agent system development framework and argumentation theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. The use of argumentation theory also indicates that the paper may be relevant to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG) and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on resolving inconsistencies between agents' beliefs suggests that it may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
